        {
          q: 'What is AEO software?',
          a: 'AEO software refers to tools that help practitioners optimise content, structured data, and brand signals for visibility within AI-generated answers. Unlike end-to-end AEO platforms, individual AEO software tools typically address one specific job: generating structured data markup, tracking brand citations in AI responses, or identifying content improvements that increase the likelihood of AI selection. Most practitioners use a combination of tools from different categories rather than a single solution.'
        },
        {
          q: 'What is the difference between AEO software and AEO platforms?',
          a: 'AEO software tools are focused and typically address a single job-to-be-done — generating schema markup, tracking AI citations, or optimising content structure. AEO platforms are broader suites that combine several of these functions, maintain persistent programme data, and often include managed service or team workflow features. Buyers with a mature programme and internal resource often find that best-in-class point tools outperform an all-in-one platform for their specific needs; buyers who need simplicity and consolidated reporting often prefer a platform.'
        },
        {
          q: 'Do I need schema markup software for AEO?',
          a: 'Structured data is one of the most reliable signals that helps AI systems understand, categorise, and cite content correctly. Schema markup tools are particularly valuable for organisations without developer resource who need to implement and maintain JSON-LD markup at scale. Even teams with developer capability benefit from dedicated schema tools that validate output, surface coverage gaps, and monitor for errors introduced by CMS updates or template changes.'
        },
        {
          q: 'How does answer tracking software work?',
          a: 'Answer tracking software works by systematically sending predefined prompts or queries to AI platforms — ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, Copilot, and others — and recording whether and how a brand or URL appears in the generated response. Because AI responses are probabilistic, good answer tracking tools run each query multiple times and aggregate results to produce statistically meaningful citation frequency estimates. The output is typically a citation rate per query, per platform, and per time period, enabling trend analysis and competitive benchmarking.'
        },
        {
          q: 'What does content optimisation software do for AEO?',
          a: 'Content optimisation software for AEO analyses existing content against the structural, semantic, and linguistic patterns that AI retrieval systems favour. This includes identifying where content lacks direct answers to questions, where structure (headings, lists, tables) could be improved, where entities are ambiguous, and where competitive content is outperforming yours as a citation source. Some tools produce content briefs; others provide in-line editing suggestions. The best tools connect content recommendations to actual citation data rather than relying on proxy metrics alone.'
        }
